IMAGE_CMD_rpi-sdimg:
# Align partitions
    BOOT_SPACE_ALIGNED=$(expr 40960 + 4096 - 1)
    BOOT_SPACE_ALIGNED=$(expr ${BOOT_SPACE_ALIGNED} - ${BOOT_SPACE_ALIGNED} % 4096)
    SDIMG_SIZE=$(expr 4096 + ${BOOT_SPACE_ALIGNED} + $ROOTFS_SIZE)

    echo "Creating filesystem with Boot partition ${BOOT_SPACE_ALIGNED} KiB and RootFS $ROOTFS_SIZE KiB"

    # Check if we are building with device tree support
    DTS="          bcm2708-rpi-zero-w.dtb     bcm2708-rpi-b.dtb     bcm2708-rpi-b-plus.dtb     bcm2709-rpi-2-b.dtb     bcm2710-rpi-3-b.dtb     bcm2710-rpi-3-b-plus.dtb     bcm2711-rpi-4-b.dtb     bcm2708-rpi-cm.dtb     bcm2710-rpi-cm3.dtb               overlays/at86rf233.dtbo     overlays/disable-bt.dtbo     overlays/dwc2.dtbo     overlays/gpio-key.dtbo     overlays/hifiberry-amp.dtbo     overlays/hifiberry-dac.dtbo     overlays/hifiberry-dacplus.dtbo     overlays/hifiberry-digi.dtbo     overlays/i2c-rtc.dtbo     overlays/iqaudio-dac.dtbo     overlays/iqaudio-dacplus.dtbo     overlays/miniuart-bt.dtbo     overlays/mcp2515-can0.dtbo     overlays/mcp2515-can1.dtbo     overlays/pitft22.dtbo     overlays/pitft28-resistive.dtbo     overlays/pitft28-capacitive.dtbo     overlays/pitft35-resistive.dtbo     overlays/pps-gpio.dtbo     overlays/rpi-ft5406.dtbo     overlays/rpi-poe.dtbo     overlays/vc4-kms-v3d.dtbo     overlays/vc4-fkms-v3d.dtbo     overlays/w1-gpio-pullup.dtbo     overlays/w1-gpio.dtbo     overlays/gpio-ir.dtbo     overlays/gpio-ir-tx.dtbo          "

    # Initialize sdcard image file
    dd if=/dev/zero of=tmp/work/raspberrypi3-poky-linux-gnueabi/core-image-minimal/1.0-r0/deploy-core-image-minimal-image-complete/core-image-minimal-raspberrypi3-20230216220654.rootfs.rpi-sdimg bs=1024 count=0 seek=${SDIMG_SIZE}

    # Create partition table
    parted -s tmp/work/raspberrypi3-poky-linux-gnueabi/core-image-minimal/1.0-r0/deploy-core-image-minimal-image-complete/core-image-minimal-raspberrypi3-20230216220654.rootfs.rpi-sdimg mklabel msdos
    # Create boot partition and mark it as bootable
    parted -s tmp/work/raspberrypi3-poky-linux-gnueabi/core-image-minimal/1.0-r0/deploy-core-image-minimal-image-complete/core-image-minimal-raspberrypi3-20230216220654.rootfs.rpi-sdimg unit KiB mkpart primary fat32 4096 $(expr ${BOOT_SPACE_ALIGNED} \+ 4096)
    parted -s tmp/work/raspberrypi3-poky-linux-gnueabi/core-image-minimal/1.0-r0/deploy-core-image-minimal-image-complete/core-image-minimal-raspberrypi3-20230216220654.rootfs.rpi-sdimg set 1 boot on
    # Create rootfs partition to the end of disk
    parted -s tmp/work/raspberrypi3-poky-linux-gnueabi/core-image-minimal/1.0-r0/deploy-core-image-minimal-image-complete/core-image-minimal-raspberrypi3-20230216220654.rootfs.rpi-sdimg -- unit KiB mkpart primary ext2 $(expr ${BOOT_SPACE_ALIGNED} \+ 4096) -1s
    parted tmp/work/raspberrypi3-poky-linux-gnueabi/core-image-minimal/1.0-r0/deploy-core-image-minimal-image-complete/core-image-minimal-raspberrypi3-20230216220654.rootfs.rpi-sdimg print

    # Create a vfat image with boot files
    BOOT_BLOCKS=$(LC_ALL=C parted -s tmp/work/raspberrypi3-poky-linux-gnueabi/core-image-minimal/1.0-r0/deploy-core-image-minimal-image-complete/core-image-minimal-raspberrypi3-20230216220654.rootfs.rpi-sdimg unit b print | awk '/ 1 / { print substr($4, 1, length($4 -1)) / 512 /2 }')
    rm -f tmp/work/raspberrypi3-poky-linux-gnueabi/core-image-minimal/1.0-r0/boot.img
    mkfs.vfat -F32 -n "raspberrypi3" -S 512 -C tmp/work/raspberrypi3-poky-linux-gnueabi/core-image-minimal/1.0-r0/boot.img $BOOT_BLOCKS
    mcopy -v -i tmp/work/raspberrypi3-poky-linux-gnueabi/core-image-minimal/1.0-r0/boot.img -s tmp/deploy/images/raspberrypi3/bootfiles/* ::/ || bbfatal "mcopy cannot copy tmp/deploy/images/raspberrypi3/bootfiles/* into boot.img"
    if [ "0" = "1" ]; then
        mcopy -v -i tmp/work/raspberrypi3-poky-linux-gnueabi/core-image-minimal/1.0-r0/boot.img -s tmp/deploy/images/raspberrypi3/armstubs/armstub7.bin ::/ || bbfatal "mcopy cannot copy tmp/deploy/images/raspberrypi3/armstubs/armstub7.bin into boot.img"
    fi
    if test -n "${DTS}"; then
        # Copy board device trees to root folder
        for dtbf in bcm2708-rpi-zero-w.dtb bcm2708-rpi-b.dtb bcm2708-rpi-b-plus.dtb bcm2709-rpi-2-b.dtb bcm2710-rpi-3-b.dtb bcm2710-rpi-3-b-plus.dtb bcm2711-rpi-4-b.dtb bcm2708-rpi-cm.dtb bcm2710-rpi-cm3.dtb; do
            dtb=`basename $dtbf`
            mcopy -v -i tmp/work/raspberrypi3-poky-linux-gnueabi/core-image-minimal/1.0-r0/boot.img -s tmp/deploy/images/raspberrypi3/$dtb ::$dtb || bbfatal "mcopy cannot copy tmp/deploy/images/raspberrypi3/$dtb into boot.img"
        done

        # Copy device tree overlays to dedicated folder
        mmd -i tmp/work/raspberrypi3-poky-linux-gnueabi/core-image-minimal/1.0-r0/boot.img overlays
        for dtbf in  overlays/at86rf233.dtbo overlays/disable-bt.dtbo overlays/dwc2.dtbo overlays/gpio-key.dtbo overlays/hifiberry-amp.dtbo overlays/hifiberry-dac.dtbo overlays/hifiberry-dacplus.dtbo overlays/hifiberry-digi.dtbo overlays/i2c-rtc.dtbo overlays/iqaudio-dac.dtbo overlays/iqaudio-dacplus.dtbo overlays/miniuart-bt.dtbo overlays/mcp2515-can0.dtbo overlays/mcp2515-can1.dtbo overlays/pitft22.dtbo overlays/pitft28-resistive.dtbo overlays/pitft28-capacitive.dtbo overlays/pitft35-resistive.dtbo overlays/pps-gpio.dtbo overlays/rpi-ft5406.dtbo overlays/rpi-poe.dtbo overlays/vc4-kms-v3d.dtbo overlays/vc4-fkms-v3d.dtbo overlays/w1-gpio-pullup.dtbo overlays/w1-gpio.dtbo overlays/gpio-ir.dtbo overlays/gpio-ir-tx.dtbo; do
            dtb=`basename $dtbf`
            mcopy -v -i tmp/work/raspberrypi3-poky-linux-gnueabi/core-image-minimal/1.0-r0/boot.img -s tmp/deploy/images/raspberrypi3/$dtb ::overlays/$dtb || bbfatal "mcopy cannot copy tmp/deploy/images/raspberrypi3/$dtb into boot.img"
        done
    fi
    if [ "${RPI_USE_U_BOOT}" = "1" ]; then
        mcopy -v -i tmp/work/raspberrypi3-poky-linux-gnueabi/core-image-minimal/1.0-r0/boot.img -s tmp/deploy/images/raspberrypi3/u-boot.bin ::kernel7.img || bbfatal "mcopy cannot copy tmp/deploy/images/raspberrypi3/u-boot.bin into boot.img"

        if [ ! -z "${INITRAMFS_IMAGE}" -a "${INITRAMFS_IMAGE_BUNDLE}" = "1" ]; then
            mcopy -v -i tmp/work/raspberrypi3-poky-linux-gnueabi/core-image-minimal/1.0-r0/boot.img -s tmp/deploy/images/raspberrypi3/zImage-initramfs-raspberrypi3.bin ::zImage || bbfatal "mcopy cannot copy tmp/deploy/images/raspberrypi3/zImage-initramfs-raspberrypi3.bin into boot.img"
        else
            mcopy -v -i tmp/work/raspberrypi3-poky-linux-gnueabi/core-image-minimal/1.0-r0/boot.img -s tmp/deploy/images/raspberrypi3/zImage ::zImage || bbfatal "mcopy cannot copy tmp/deploy/images/raspberrypi3/zImage into boot.img"
        fi
    else
        if [ ! -z "${INITRAMFS_IMAGE}" -a "${INITRAMFS_IMAGE_BUNDLE}" = "1" ]; then
            mcopy -v -i tmp/work/raspberrypi3-poky-linux-gnueabi/core-image-minimal/1.0-r0/boot.img -s tmp/deploy/images/raspberrypi3/zImage-initramfs-raspberrypi3.bin ::kernel7.img || bbfatal "mcopy cannot copy tmp/deploy/images/raspberrypi3/zImage-initramfs-raspberrypi3.bin into boot.img"
        else
            mcopy -v -i tmp/work/raspberrypi3-poky-linux-gnueabi/core-image-minimal/1.0-r0/boot.img -s tmp/deploy/images/raspberrypi3/zImage ::kernel7.img || bbfatal "mcopy cannot copy tmp/deploy/images/raspberrypi3/zImage into boot.img"
        fi
    fi

    # Add files (eg. hypervisor binaries) from the deploy dir
    if [ -n "${DEPLOYPAYLOAD}" ] ; then
        echo "Copying deploy file payload into VFAT"
        for entry in ${DEPLOYPAYLOAD} ; do
            # Split entry at optional ':' to enable file renaming for the destination
            if [ $(echo "$entry" | grep -c :) = "0" ] ; then
                DEPLOY_FILE="$entry"
                DEST_FILENAME="$entry"
            else
                DEPLOY_FILE="$(echo "$entry" | cut -f1 -d:)"
                DEST_FILENAME="$(echo "$entry" | cut -f2- -d:)"
            fi
            mcopy -v -i tmp/work/raspberrypi3-poky-linux-gnueabi/core-image-minimal/1.0-r0/boot.img -s tmp/deploy/images/raspberrypi3/${DEPLOY_FILE} ::${DEST_FILENAME} || bbfatal "mcopy cannot copy tmp/deploy/images/raspberrypi3/${DEPLOY_FILE} into boot.img"
        done
    fi

    if [ -n "" ] ; then

SDK_POST_INSTALL_COMMAND_task-populate-s:
printf "\nExtracting buildtools...\n"
	cd $target_sdk_dir
	env_setup_script="$target_sdk_dir/environment-setup-cortexa7t2hf-neon-vfpv4-poky-linux-gnueabi"
        if [ -n "${SDK_BUILDTOOLS_INSTALLER}" ]; then
		printf "buildtools\ny" | ./${SDK_BUILDTOOLS_INSTALLER} > buildtools.log || { printf 'ERROR: buildtools installation failed:\n' ; cat buildtools.log ; echo "printf 'ERROR: this SDK was not fully installed and needs reinstalling\n'" >> $env_setup_script ; exit 1 ; }

		# Delete the buildtools tar file since it won't be used again
		rm -f ./${SDK_BUILDTOOLS_INSTALLER}
		# We don't need the log either since it succeeded
		rm -f buildtools.log

		# Make sure when the user sets up the environment, they also get
		# the buildtools-tarball tools in their path.
		echo ". $target_sdk_dir/buildtools/environment-setup*" >> $env_setup_script
	fi

	# Allow bitbake environment setup to be ran as part of this sdk.
	echo "export OE_SKIP_SDK_CHECK=1" >> $env_setup_script
	# Work around runqemu not knowing how to get this information within the eSDK
	echo "export DEPLOY_DIR_IMAGE=$target_sdk_dir/tmp/deploy/images/raspberrypi3" >> $env_setup_script

	# A bit of another hack, but we need this in the path only for devtool
	# so put it at the end of $PATH.
	echo "export PATH=$target_sdk_dir/sysroots/x86_64-pokysdk-linux/usr/bin:\$PATH" >> $env_setup_script

	echo "printf 'SDK environment now set up; additionally you may now run devtool to perform development tasks.\nRun devtool --help for further details.\n'" >> $env_setup_script

	# Warn if trying to use external bitbake and the ext SDK together
	echo "(which bitbake > /dev/null 2>&1 && echo 'WARNING: attempting to use the extensible SDK in an environment set up to run bitbake - this may lead to unexpected results. Please source this script in a new shell session instead.') || true" >> $env_setup_script

	if [ "$prepare_buildsystem" != "no" -a -n "${SDK_BUILDTOOLS_INSTALLER}" ]; then
		printf "Preparing build system...\n"
		# dash which is /bin/sh on Ubuntu will not preserve the
		# current working directory when first ran, nor will it set $1 when
		# sourcing a script. That is why this has to look so ugly.
		LOGFILE="$target_sdk_dir/preparing_build_system.log"
		sh -c ". buildtools/environment-setup* > $LOGFILE && cd $target_sdk_dir/`dirname ${oe_init_build_env_path}` && set $target_sdk_dir && . $target_sdk_dir/${oe_init_build_env_path} $target_sdk_dir >> $LOGFILE && python3 $target_sdk_dir/ext-sdk-prepare.py $LOGFILE ''" || { echo "printf 'ERROR: this SDK was not fully installed and needs reinstalling\n'" >> $env_setup_script ; exit 1 ; }
	fi
	if [ -e $target_sdk_dir/ext-sdk-prepare.py ]; then
		rm $target_sdk_dir/ext-sdk-prepare.py
	fi
	echo done
SDK_PRE_INSTALL_COMMAND_task-populate-sd:
# Since bitbake won't run as root it doesn't make sense to try and install
	# the extensible sdk as root.
	if [ "`id -u`" = "0" ]; then
		echo "ERROR: The extensible sdk cannot be installed as root."
		exit 1
	fi
	if ! command -v locale > /dev/null; then
		echo "ERROR: The installer requires the locale command, please install it first"
		exit 1
	fi
        # Check setting of LC_ALL set above
	canonicalised_locale=`echo $LC_ALL | sed 's/UTF-8/utf8/'`
	if ! locale -a | grep -q $canonicalised_locale ; then
		echo "ERROR: the installer requires the $LC_ALL locale to be installed (but not selected), please install it first"
		exit 1
	fi
	# The relocation script used by buildtools installer requires python
	if ! command -v python3 > /dev/null; then
		echo "ERROR: The installer requires python3, please install it first"
		exit 1
	fi
	missing_utils=""
	for util in ${SDK_REQUIRED_UTILITIES}; do
		if ! command -v $util > /dev/null; then
			missing_utils="$missing_utils $util"
		fi
	done
	if [ -n "$missing_utils" ] ; then
		echo "ERROR: the SDK requires the following missing utilities, please install them: $missing_utils"
		exit 1
	fi
	SDK_EXTENSIBLE="1"
	if [ "$publish" = "1" ] && [ "full" = "minimal" ] ; then
		EXTRA_TAR_OPTIONS="$EXTRA_TAR_OPTIONS --exclude=sstate-cache"
	fi
